brary_coverage.py:77:        \\\"--coordinates\\\",\\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:79:        help=\\\"Maven coordinates Group:Artifact:Version for the target library\\\",\\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:141:        group, artifact, version = flags.coordinates.split(\\\":\\\")\\n./forge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:144:            f\\\"ERROR: Invalid coordinates format: {flags.coordinates}. Expected Group:Artifact:Version\\\",\\n./tests/src/org.antlr/ST4/4.0.8/build.gradle:11:String libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_fails.py:11:    --coordinates group:artifact:oldVersion \\\\\\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_fails.py:17:    --coordinates group:artifact:oldVersion \\\\\\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_fails.py:50:        \\\"--coordinates\\\",\\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_fails.py:52:        help=\\\"Maven coordinates Group:Artifact:Version for the current library version\\\",\\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_fails.py:90:        \\\"--coordinates\\\",\\n./forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_fails.py:91:        flags.coordinates,\\n./tests/src/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpmime/4.1/gradle.properties:1:# Optional explicit tested library coordinates (format: group:artifact:version).\\n./tests/src/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpmime/4.1/gradle.properties:4:library.coordinates = org.apache.httpcomponents:httpmime:4.1\\n./tests/src/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpmime/4.3/build.gradle:11:String libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\\n./tests/src/org.slf4j/jcl-over-slf4j/1.5.6/gradle.properties:1:# Optional explicit tested library coordinates (format: group:artifact:version).\\n./tests/src/org.slf4j/jcl-over-slf4j/1.5.6/gradle.properties:4:library.coordinates = org.slf4j:jcl-over-slf4j:1.5.6\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:45:./gradlew generateMetadata --coordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:51:./gradlew generateMetadata --coordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0 --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:52:./gradlew generateMetadata --coordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0 --agentAllowedPackages=com.example.pkg,org.acme.lib\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:77:./gradlew scaffold --coordinates com.example:my-library:1.0.0\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:83:./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:105:* `requires`: An array of `groupId:artifactId` coordinates for libraries this metadata depends on.\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:159:  --coordinates=all \\\\\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:168:  --coordinates=all \\\\\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:177:  --coordinates=all \\\\\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:216:./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.example:library:0.0.1\\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:266: * `<groupId>` and `<artifactId>` - part of the standard Maven coordinates ([see this](https://maven.apache.org/pom.html#Maven_Coordinates))\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:54:- Compilation, JVM-mode tests (`javaTest`), and native-image tests (`nativeTest`).\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:57:The harness uses a single coordinates filter `-Pcoordinates=` accepting `all`, `group:artifact`, `group:artifact:version`, or shard `k/n`. It also exposes authoring helpers (`generateMetadata`, `splitTestOnlyMetadata`, `fixTestNativeImageRun`, `addTestedVersion`, `fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`), reporting tasks (`jacocoTestReport`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `generateLibraryStats`, `analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess`), and the `package` release task. The full task reference lives in [DEVELOPING.md](DEVELOPING.md).\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:102:| `fails-javac-compile` | Issue | New-version compatibility failed during the `compileTestJava` / Java compilation stage. |\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:103:| `fails-java-run` | Issue | New-version compatibility failed during the `javaTest` / JVM runtime stage. |\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:172:If neither matches and the user has enabled `useLatestVersion` on the query (Gradle: `useLatestMetadataVersion()`), the plugin falls back to the entry with `latest: true` (at most one per file, FR-M-6). Otherwise no metadata is loaded for that coordinate. `skipped-versions` is consumed by the test harness and the libraries-and-frameworks page, not by the plugin at native-image time.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:181:    DefaultFor -- no --> UseLatestOpt{\\\"Query has<br/><code>useLatestVersion</code>?\\\"}\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:215:- **FR-T-5** Tests must compile under JDK 25 and pass both `javaTest` and `nativeTest` lanes on every JDK/OS combination listed in `ci.json`.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:251:- **NFR-2 Isolation.** Per-coordinate test execution must not depend on or affect other coordinates' build outputs.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:255:- **NFR-6 Sharded scalability.** Any Gradle task that accepts `-Pcoordinates=` must accept `k/n` shards so CI can parallelize. The harness must handle adding a new library without code changes (purely metadata-driven discovery).\\n./tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-jdk14/1.5.6/build.gradle:11:String libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\\n./docs/CI.md:57:For normal user-created issues, the `library-new-request` label from the issue template makes the workflow eligible for triage. For automated issues created by native-build-tools without labels, such as issues opened by non-maintainers, the workflow first checks whether the issue has no labels, uses the standard `Support for groupId:artifactId:version` title, and contains a `### Full Maven coordinates` section. If it matches that shape, the workflow adds `library-new-request` and `priority` before continuing.\\n./docs/CI.md:59:Once eligible, the workflow extracts the requested Maven coordinates, validates the `groupId:artifactId:version` format, closes invalid requests, closes duplicate exact-coordinate requests, and closes requests for versions already supported by the repository. If the request remains eligible, it generates a deps.dev dependency graph and opens or reuses `library-new-request` issues for unsupported transitive dependencies, linking them as blockers of the original request.\\n./tests/src/org.antlr/ST4/4.0.8/gradle.properties:1:# Optional explicit tested library coordinates (format: group:artifact:version).\\n./tests/src/org.antlr/ST4/4.0.8/gradle.properties:4:library.coordinates = org.antlr:ST4:4.0.8\\n./tests/src/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpmime/4.3/gradle.properties:1:# Optional explicit tested library coordinates (format: group:artifact:version).\\n./tests/src/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpmime/4.3/gradle.properties:4:library.coordinates = org.apache.httpcomponents:httpmime:4.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:57:   ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:61:   ./gradlew validateIndexFiles -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:65:   ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:69:   ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:74:GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:79:To exercise many tests at once, you can target all coordinates or a slice of the test space via the N/M shard syntax.\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:81:All coordinates:\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:84:    ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=all\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:85:    ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=all\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:86:    ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=all\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:91:    ./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=1/16\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:92:    ./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=1/16\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:93:    ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=1/16\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:96:### Listing available coordinates\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:98:To print all testable GAV coordinates while honoring the same -Pcoordinates filter semantics used by the harness:\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:101:./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=all\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:102:./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=group:artifact\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:103:./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:104:./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=1/16\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:105:./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=group:artifact -PstrictCoordinates=true\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:108:In GitHub Actions, this task also writes a space-separated list to the GITHUB_OUTPUT key \\\"coordinates\\\".\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:113:To print deps.dev dependency graphs for resolved GAV coordinates while honoring the same `-Pcoordinates` filter semantics used by the harness:\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:116:./gradlew generateDependencyGraph -Pcoordinates=all\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:117:./gradlew generateDependencyGraph -Pcoordinates=group:artifact\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:118:./gradlew generateDependencyGraph -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:119:./gradlew generateDependencyGraph -Pcoordinates=1/16\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:126:Each stage of the testing can be run with `-Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`. Here are the examples:\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:128:./gradlew clean -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:129:./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:130:./gradlew validateIndexFiles -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:131:./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:132:./gradlew checkstyle -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:133:./gradlew compileTestJava -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:134:./gradlew javaTest -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:135:./gradlew nativeTestCompile -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:136:./gradlew listLibraryJars -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:137:./gradlew generateDynamicAccessReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:138:./gradlew generateLibraryStats -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:140:./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:149:./gradlew jacocoTestReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:151:The root jacocoTestReport is a harness wrapper that invokes the per-project task across matching coordinates.\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:174:./gradlew generateLibraryStats -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all]\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:178:- `generateLibraryStats`: recomputes selected coordinates and updates matching exploded stats files under `stats/`.\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:185:./gradlew analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess --coordinates=group:artifact:version\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:194:- `coordinates`: group:artifact:version (single coordinate only)\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:199:   ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:200:   ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3 --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:201:   ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3 --agentAllowedPackages=org.example.app,com.acme.service\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:211:./gradlew nativeTraceImage -Pcoordinates=<group:artifact:version>\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:218:  -Pcoordinates=<group:artifact:version> \\\\\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:235:  -Pcoordinates=<group:artifact:version> \\\\\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:245:./gradlew splitTestOnlyMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:246:./gradlew splitTestOnlyMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:247:./gradlew splitTestOnlyMetadata -Pcoordinates=1/16\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:258:- -PtestLibraryCoordinates=group:artifact:version (coordinates of an existing tested version whose tests you run)\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:289:    ./gradlew addTestedVersion -Pcoordinates=\\\"group:artifact:newVersion\\\" --lastSupportedVersion=\\\"oldVersion\\\"\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:293:    ./gradlew addTestedVersion -Pcoordinates=\\\"org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.4\\\" --lastSupportedVersion=\\\"42.7.3\\\"\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:307:- Pull images (single lib): `./gradlew pullAllowedDockerImages -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:308:- Check metadata (single lib): `./gradlew checkMetadataFiles -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:309:- Generate metadata (single lib): `./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:310:- Build trace-enabled native image: `./gradlew nativeTraceImage -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:311:- Run trace-enabled native image: `./gradlew runNativeTraceImage -Pcoordinates=group:artifact:version -PtraceMetadataPath=<absolute-trace-output-dir> -PtraceMetadataConditionPackages=<package1,package2,...>`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:313:- Split test-only metadata: `./gradlew splitTestOnlyMetadata -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all]`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:315:- Test (single lib): `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:316:- List resolved tested-library jars: `./gradlew listLibraryJars -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:317:- Generate dynamic access report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:318:- Generate dynamic access coverage report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:321:- Coverage (single lib): `./gradlew jacocoTestReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:322:- Generate library stats: `./gradlew generateLibraryStats -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all]`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:324:- List available coordinates: `./gradlew listCoordinates -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all] [-PstrictCoordinates=true]`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:325:- Generate dependency graph: `./gradlew generateDependencyGraph -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all]`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:326:- Analyze external dynamic access: `./gradlew analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess --coordinates=group:artifact:version`\\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:330:- Record a newly tested version: `./gradlew addTestedVersion -Pcoordinates=\\\"group:artifact:newVersion\\\" --lastSupportedVersion=\\\"oldVersion\\\"`\\n./README.md:4:[![Tested library versions](https://img.shields.io/badge/dynamic/json.svg?label=tested%20library%20versions&query=%24.badges.testedLibraryVersions&url=https%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Foracle%2Fgraalvm-reachability-metadata%2Fstats%2Fcoverage%2Flatest%2Fbadges.json&style=flat-square&color=BF8700)](COVERAGE.md)\\n./README.md:28:Open a [library-request ticket](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/new?template=01_support_new_library.yml), include the Maven coordinates, and our automation will take it from there (🤖).\\n./README.md:32:Open an [update ticket](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/issues/new?template=02_update_existing_library.yml) and include the Maven coordinates of the library that needs changes.\\n./tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-jdk14/1.5.6/gradle.properties:1:# Optional explicit tested library coordinates (format: group:artifact:version).\\n./tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-jdk14/1.5.6/gradle.properties:4:library.coordinates = org.slf4j:slf4j-jdk14:1.5.6\\n./tests/src/io.dropwizard.metrics5/metrics-core/5.0.1/build.gradle:11:String libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\\n./tests/src/com.barchart.udt/barchart-udt-bundle/2.3.0/build.gradle:11:String libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\\n./tests/src/org.slf4j/slf4j-jdk14/1.6.0/build.gradle:11:String libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\\n./build.gradle:153:        [name: name, args: [gradleCmd, name, \\\"-Pcoordinates=${target}\\\"]]\\n./build.gradle:190:                        Options: -Pc